Hi both,

Fieldwork closed yesterday. 1,180 completes, clean data file exported this morning.

A few notes on variables that came up during QA:

1. skincare_routine_enjoyment: measured on a 5-point scale from 1 ("dislikes skincare routines") to 5 ("always_cleanses_morning_and_night"). Distribution skews positive — peak at 4 ("enjoys routine but skips occasionally").

2. sc_brand_awareness: binary (yes/no) per brand. Captures aided awareness — "Have you heard of [brand]?" Shown after the brand name is displayed, not spontaneous recall.

3. sc_brand_consideration: also binary. "Would you consider buying [brand]?" — strictly applied as a post-awareness filter only.

4. n_skincare_steps_per_day: integer, self-reported. Range 0-10. Median is 3. Heavier users (5+ steps) skew strongly female and in the 25-34 age group.

5. The channel variable captures where respondents last purchased skincare products. Top channels in this demo dataset: drugstore_chain_a (36%), drugstore_chain_b (21%), online (19%), pharmacy (12%), premium_beauty_retailer (7%).

6. Gender split: 61% female, 37% male, 2% non-binary or prefer not to say. Age distribution peaks at 25-34 (27%) and 35-44 (23%).

7. Income brackets run from below_20000 up to 100000_or_more. The 35000_to_49999 bracket has the largest share at 29%.

One data quality note: 14 respondents had missing data on annual_hh_income. These were coded as "prefer_not_to_answer" rather than dropped. This affects sample_base for income-filtered queries.

Data file is on the shared demo drive at /shared/data/demo/. Let me know if you need any re-cuts.

